[4] Cholera - Malawi: (Southern Province)
Date: Tue 15 Jan 2008
Source: Reuters Africa [edited]
<http://africa.reuters.com/top/news/usnBAN540674.html>


The health minister said on Tuesday [15 Jan 2008] 8 people have died
from an outbreak of cholera in southern Malawi, where flooding has
increased the risk of contracting the disease,

"Floods are worsening the situation because in rural areas people are
unable to satisfy the most basic human needs like hygiene, proper
sanitation, and safe drinking water," health minister Marjorie
Ngaunje told Reuters in an interview. "But we are trying to teach
people to wash their hands, boil water, and other important
information to help prevent the disease."

Ngaunje said there were 291 reported cases of cholera in the past 3
weeks in the southern part of Malawi, one of the poorest nations in
Africa. "In (the) 2001/02 rainy season we recorded 33 546 cases with
953 deaths, in the 2003/04 season we had 959 cases but only 13 people
died and in 2006/07 only 6 people died out of 309 reported cases," she said.

[Byline: Mabvuto Banda]

