[6] Cholera - Viet Nam: (Hanoi), vaccination program
Date: Tue 15 Jan 2008
Source: Thanh Nien News [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/healthy/?catid=8&newsid=35043>


Nearly 400 000 individuals in Thanh Xuan and Hoang Mai districts in
Hanoi will receive free vaccinations against cholera before the Lunar
New Year, or Tet holiday. The announcement came on Sunday [13 Jan
2008] from the National Institute of Hygiene and Epidemiology.

According to experts, this is the 1st time in the last 20 years that
the health agency has taken such a preventive measure in controlling
the epidemic in Hanoi. Vaccination gives good protection against
cholera within 6 months of the injection and has a 60-70 percent rate
of effectiveness.

[Byline: Nam Son]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This immunization program underscores the significance of cholera's
role in the outbreak of diarrhea that has affected Viet Nam,
primarily in the northern parts. A map showing the location of Hanoi
in northern Viet Nam can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/mekong.pdf>.

The outbreaks discussed in this update can also be located on the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://www.healthmap.org/promed>. - Mod.LL]
